<h1>LiveGather Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>LiveGather is a real-time geophoto sharing community that is intended to
connect people through the open sharing of photos. You do not need to be a
member to view content on LiveGather; however, you must create an account to
post content to LiveGather.</p>

<h2>Information Collection and Use</h2>

<p>All photos and information that you post to LiveGather will be made
available to the public for anyone to access. The ability to openly share and
connect with people is what makes the Internet great; however, <strong>do not
post content that you do not want to be made public</strong>.</p>

<p>We may use information that you provide (i.e. your photo, location, tags,
caption, and comments) to more accurately deliver advertisements.</p>

<h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>

<p>When you create an account using your Twitter, Facebook, Yahoo, or Google
account, you are allowing a connection to be made between LiveGather and said
service.</p>

<p>You may choose to have your photos instantly shared to Twitter and Facebook
as they are posted to LiveGather. If you choose to do this, then you are
giving your content to another service and we recommend you read their privacy
policy before doing so to see how your content will be handled.</p>

<h2>Managing Your Information</h2>

<p>You may delete photos that you have uploaded by signing in and going to your
profile and then clicking &ldquo;delete&rdquo;  next to the photo.</p>

<p>You may manage your account settings (i.e. email, default location,
notification settings) by clicking &ldquo;account&rdquo; in the header.</p>

<h1>When using LiveGather, you are subject to the <a href="/tos">LiveGather
Terms of Service</a>.</h1>
